<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF4A6AF5F82C9133176CB3A9" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF4A6AF5F82C9133176CB3A9" blockId="177.[1998,2591,1779,2203]" pageId="177" pageNumber="939">
Subgenus Pizonyx; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4A6AF5F7279133174ABCB5" baseAuthorityName="E. Geoffroy" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[2267,2378,1898,1927]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albescens">albescens</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4A6AF5F82C91D416B7BC9C" authorityName="G. G. Goodwin" authorityYear="1955" box="[2000,2231,1933,1966]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cobanensis">Myotis cobanensis</taxonomicName>
is known only from two specimens; it was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4A6AF5F74991851734BCCF" baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[2229,2356,2012,2045]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="velifer">M. velifer</taxonomicName>
and later raised to a distinct species based on morphology. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4A6AF5F82C9E7616B3B37E" authorityName="G. G. Goodwin" authorityYear="1955" box="[2000,2227,2095,2124]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="177" pageNumber="939" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cobanensis">Myotis cobanensis</taxonomicName>
has not been included in any molecular analysis, and its taxonomic status is doubtful. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
